# Materials Sources

## LEDs
Ben purchased the original set of IR LEDs from Core Electronics, allowed purchase of through-hole nIR components as single items
https://core-electronics.com.au/search/?q=infrared+led

Another AU supplier with a much more extensive range, including some pretty nice looking SMD nIR components for use on a PCB:
RS Components:  https://au.rs-online.com/web/c/displays-optoelectronics/leds-led-accessories/ir-leds/

## Software Issues
Chris mentioned that there was a bit of a sticking point interfacing between python and the web streaming front-end for the current setup.
Flask may be a lightweight python-based server framework that may solve some of these problems:
https://projects.raspberrypi.org/en/projects/python-web-server-with-flask
https://www.meccanismocomplesso.org/en/flask-un-web-server-in-python-su-raspberry/
